															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/stormbreath" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3075960); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3075960&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164616" alt="stormbreath" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3075960)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/stormbreath" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3075960); return false;" >stormbreath</a></span> <span class="odate time_1512194994 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Dec 2017 06:09</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3644148">
									

<p>Adebowale is not meant to have bad English - most of those are typos.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Thank&nbsp;you&nbsp;for&nbsp;looking&nbsp;this&nbsp;over</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>This bit doesn't to show up in any other AWCY format, though I'll forgive it as nobody can seem to agree on what exactly the format is.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is an intentional, small deviation from the normal AWCY format (l'd compare it to an SCP having a <strong>Discovery</strong> section, because the entire piece comes in two parts, and I'd thought it would be good to distinguish them. The creation section is needed once, while the performance is needed any time the song is played.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Kinda seems like poetic prose, but I don't know.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Poetic prose, it's not meant to be really be an accurate sentence.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Not entirely sure how I'd fix this one, though I do understand what it's trying to say.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I wrote it, noticed it sounded a bit weird, and tried to think about how to fix it. I wasn't sure of how to do it, but the sentence was parsible and the meaning could be discerned, so I kept it.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>It was a basic kindness? Not sure if this is just prose or not.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>It's not really prose, I'm pretty sure the sentence is still gramatically accurate the way I wrote it. I don't think kindness needs an article.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

